WEBVTT

00:01.417 --> 00:03.792
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOUR MOTHER IS STILL
GETTING DRESSED.

00:03.792 --> 00:05.166
WHAT IS SHE
DOIN' UP THERE?

00:05.166 --> 00:07.792
WELL, THERE'S A WHOLE
LOT MORE OF HER
TO DRESS THESE DAYS.

00:07.792 --> 00:11.000
SO NOT  WHAT TO SAY
TO A WOMAN WHO'S
2 WEEKS OVERDUE.

00:11.000 --> 00:12.500
SHE'S RIGHT, DAWSON.
YOU SAY, "DARLING,

00:12.500 --> 00:15.875
I'VE NEVER SEEN
A WOMAN WITH A 65" WAIST
LOOK SO HOT."

00:15.875 --> 00:17.417
YOU GUYS
ARE TERRIBLE.

00:17.417 --> 00:19.792
WHAT WOULD BE TERRIBLE
IS MISSING OUR RESERVATION.

00:19.792 --> 00:20.792
THIS MAY BE OUR LAST DATE
BEFORE THE BABY COMES,

00:20.792 --> 00:22.875
AND IF WE DON'T HURRY--

00:22.875 --> 00:25.834
MITCH,
WE HAVE TO GO. NOW.

00:25.834 --> 00:27.000
YOU'RE TELLING ME?
WE'RE LATE ALREADY.

00:27.000 --> 00:28.875
NO. FORGET ABOUT DINNER.

00:28.875 --> 00:30.208
NOW?

00:30.208 --> 00:31.583
NOW.
NOW?

00:31.583 --> 00:32.583
UH-HUH. IF WE
DON'T GET MOVING,

00:32.583 --> 00:33.583
YEAH, RIGHT HERE
ON THE STAIRS.

00:33.583 --> 00:34.166
OK. HOW LONG ARE
YOUR CONTRACTIONS?

00:34.166 --> 00:36.083
LONG ENOUGH TO HURT.

00:36.083 --> 00:36.500
AAH! AAH! HERE.

00:36.500 --> 00:38.417
AAH!

00:38.417 --> 00:39.375
I GOT THE BAG.

00:39.375 --> 00:40.375
DID YOU PACK MY BATHROBE?

00:40.375 --> 00:41.417
FLANNEL.
HEAVY SOCKS?

00:41.417 --> 00:42.834
WOOL.
LIP BALM?

00:42.834 --> 00:43.875
DAMN!
I KNEW I FORGOT
SOMETHING.

00:43.875 --> 00:44.834
WHAT, ARE YOU GUYS
GOING SKIING?

00:44.834 --> 00:45.708
I'M GONNA PANT
FOR A FEW HOURS. AAH!

00:45.708 --> 00:46.834
HERE.

00:46.834 --> 00:47.708
AH, THANKS.
WE SHOULD CALL
THE DOCTOR.

00:47.708 --> 00:48.500
FROM THE CAR.

00:48.500 --> 00:49.417
WE'LL CALL YOU,
TOO, SON.

00:49.417 --> 00:50.291
DID YOU REMEMBER
THE BIRTHING MUSIC?

00:50.291 --> 00:53.959
I GOT ENYA,
JOHN TESH, KENNY G.

00:53.959 --> 00:57.166
I'M HAVING A BABY,
NOT GOING INTO A COMA.

00:58.125 --> 01:02.375
[MITCH AND GALE BICKERING]

01:02.375 --> 01:05.166
WELL, I GUESS THAT
PRETTY MUCH DOES IT
FOR OUR EVENING.

01:05.166 --> 01:06.458
PRETTY MUCH.
YEAH.

01:06.458 --> 01:07.792
HA HA HA!

01:07.792 --> 01:08.792
HA!

01:08.792 --> 01:10.000
[SQUEALS]

01:57.917 --> 01:59.625
IT'S NOT HAPPENING?

01:59.625 --> 02:00.708
THEY'RE CALLED
BRAXTON HICKS CONTRACTIONS.

02:00.708 --> 02:02.917
FALSE LABOR.

02:02.917 --> 02:06.250
TRUST ME. THERE IS
NOTHING FALSE ABOUT
THESE CONTRACTIONS.

02:06.250 --> 02:09.291
YOU'RE RIGHT, BUT
THEY'RE NOT ENOUGH
TO BRING ON DILATION.

02:09.291 --> 02:11.041
YOU'RE STILL AT
1 CENTIMETER, GALE.

02:11.041 --> 02:13.291
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE
USING THE RIGHT RULER?

02:14.625 --> 02:16.959
SO, I TAKE IT
THERE'S NO BABY YET?

02:16.959 --> 02:18.959
MM-MMM.

02:18.959 --> 02:20.750
THE BABY MAY DECIDE
NOT TO MAKE AN
APPEARANCE FOR DAYS.

02:20.750 --> 02:21.917
Dawson: REALLY?

02:21.917 --> 02:24.625
NORMALLY, I'D HAVE
NO CAUSE FOR CONCERN.

02:24.625 --> 02:25.625
BUT YOU DO.

02:25.625 --> 02:26.959
BECAUSE OF GALE'S AGE,

02:26.959 --> 02:29.458
THERE'S A SIGNIFICANTLY
INCREASED RISK
OF COMPLICATIONS.

02:29.458 --> 02:30.708
WHAT KIND OF
COMPLICATIONS?

02:30.708 --> 02:31.708
NOW, I DON'T WANT
ANYONE TO WORRY.

02:31.708 --> 02:32.792
THEN TELL US WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

02:32.792 --> 02:35.583
IF STAGE 2 LABOR DOESN'T
BEGIN IN A FEW DAYS,

02:35.583 --> 02:36.583
I'M GOING TO INDUCE,

02:36.583 --> 02:39.250
AND IF ANY ISSUES ARISE,

02:39.250 --> 02:41.125
WE'VE GOT A GREAT
FACILITY HERE TO DO
AN IMMEDIATE "C."

02:41.125 --> 02:43.291
OH, MY GOD.

02:43.291 --> 02:45.583
DO YOU REALLY THINK THAT
IT'S GONNA BE NECESSARY?

02:45.583 --> 02:46.875
JUST RELAX.

02:46.875 --> 02:48.625
HONESTLY, THAT'S
THE BEST THING
YOU CAN DO RIGHT NOW.

02:48.625 --> 02:51.500
ISN'T THERE ANYTHING
YOU CAN DO TO HELP
THE BABY ALONG?

02:51.500 --> 02:55.166
SOME OF MY PATIENTS TRY
TALKING TO THEIR BABIES.

02:55.166 --> 02:56.625
WHAT'S YOUR BABY'S NAME?

02:58.375 --> 03:00.291
THAT'S A VERY GOOD QUESTION.

03:00.291 --> 03:04.166
WE HAVEN'T QUITE FOUND
THE RIGHT ONE YET.

03:04.166 --> 03:05.625
I'M GONNA WRITE YOU
A PRESCRIPTION, GALE,

03:05.625 --> 03:09.667
AND THEN I'M GONNA
GO BACK TO DINNER
WITH MY HUSBAND.

03:09.667 --> 03:11.625
YOU DO THE SAME.

03:13.667 --> 03:17.000
"NAME YOUR BABY."

03:17.000 --> 03:18.250
THIS ASSIGNMENT IS
ALL KINDS OF STUPID.

03:18.250 --> 03:20.417
THE STORY DOESN'T
EVEN HAVE A HERO.

03:20.417 --> 03:23.333
MOST GOOD STORIES HAVE
A HERO OF SOME SORT.

03:23.333 --> 03:27.375
BUT EVERYBODY IN HERE
HAS ALL THESE PROBLEMS.

03:27.375 --> 03:30.375
ACTUALLY, WILL, THE MOST
INTERESTING HEROES
USUALLY HAVE A PROBLEM

03:30.375 --> 03:32.208
THEY CAN'T OVERCOME,
DESPITE THEMSELVES.

03:32.208 --> 03:34.375
LIKE PATHOLOGICAL
TARDINESS.

03:34.375 --> 03:37.542
BUT MANY HEROES DO EVENTUALLY
OVERCOME THEIR FLAWS.

03:37.542 --> 03:38.500
YEAH. I'LL BELIEVE IT
WHEN I SEE IT.

03:38.500 --> 03:40.458
THEY JUST HAVE TO
LEARN HOW TO AVOID

03:40.458 --> 03:41.417
FRIDAY NIGHT TRAFFIC
ON WATER STREET.

03:41.417 --> 03:42.458
OH, THEY DIDN'T
LEARN THAT LAST WEEK?

03:42.458 --> 03:44.583
THEY GOT STUCK ON
FRONT STREET LAST WEEK.

03:44.583 --> 03:46.542
IF YOU TWO DON'T MIND,

03:46.542 --> 03:49.250
I'M TRYIN' TO PASS
THE FOURTH GRADE HERE.

03:49.250 --> 03:51.291
HA HA HA HA!

03:51.291 --> 03:52.458
OK.

03:54.750 --> 03:55.875
HEY, GUESS WHO?

03:55.875 --> 03:58.000
I WAS JUST CALLIN' TO
SEE IF YOU WERE BACK YET,

03:58.000 --> 04:00.333
BUT ALAS, NO BEAU.

04:00.333 --> 04:02.750
SO WHEN YOU GET THIS,
GIVE ME A CALL.

04:02.750 --> 04:05.041
OK. BYE.

04:05.041 --> 04:07.375
Bessie: OK.
IT'S OFFICIAL.

04:07.375 --> 04:10.041
YOU'VE BECOME THE
NEUROTIC GIRLFRIEND.

04:10.041 --> 04:12.625
IT'S JUST--IT'S WEIRD.

04:12.625 --> 04:14.125
THERE'S NOTHING
WEIRD ABOUT IT.

04:14.125 --> 04:16.916
HE'S AWAY ON
A FISHING TRIP
WITH HIS BROTHER.

04:18.000 --> 04:21.834
I FOUND THE MOST
ADORABLE ONESIE DOWNTOWN.

04:21.834 --> 04:24.125
I JUST HAD TO
GET IT FOR GALE.

04:24.125 --> 04:26.375
HELP ME WRAP IT.

04:26.375 --> 04:27.917
I'M GOIN' TO PACEY'S.

04:27.917 --> 04:30.000
Bessie: JOEY.

04:30.000 --> 04:32.000
WHAT'S A NAMING SHOWER?

04:32.000 --> 04:35.500
YOU KNOW, INSTEAD OF BOOTIES,
EVERYBODY BRINGS NAMES.

04:35.500 --> 04:36.875
YOU PEOPLE LOVE
TO INVENT RITUALS.

04:36.875 --> 04:38.917
HEH HEH!

04:38.917 --> 04:40.917
IT'S TOMORROW AFTERNOON.
CAN YOU MAKE IT?

04:40.917 --> 04:41.917
TOMORROW? ABSOLUTELY.

04:41.917 --> 04:43.208
THE DAY AFTER,

04:43.208 --> 04:45.417
I'M ON THE NOON TRAIN
TO BOSTON.

04:45.417 --> 04:47.083
WHAT'S IN BOSTON?

04:47.083 --> 04:50.667
WELL, IF MY INTERVIEW
FOR CAMBRIDGE MAGAZINE
GOES WELL, ME.

04:50.667 --> 04:53.125
CAMBRIDGE MAGAZINE?

04:53.125 --> 04:54.291
YEAH. THEY JUST CALLED

04:54.291 --> 04:55.417
RIGHT BEFORE
YOU CAME OVER.

04:55.417 --> 04:57.750
I APPLIED
FOR THIS INTERVIEW

04:57.750 --> 04:59.333
AS AN ASSISTANT
LIFESTYLES EDITOR,

04:59.333 --> 05:01.083
AND THEY LOVED
MY APPLICATION.

05:01.083 --> 05:02.375
THEY'RE ACTUALLY
THINKING OF PAYING ME

05:02.375 --> 05:04.291
TO GO TO CONCERTS AND
MUSEUMS AND RESTAURANTS.

05:04.291 --> 05:06.417
IS THAT AMAZING OR WHAT?

05:06.417 --> 05:08.000
WOW.

05:09.125 --> 05:12.041
SPEAK YOUR SUBTEXT, BOY.

05:12.041 --> 05:15.875
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT YOU
WERE APPLYING FOR A JOB.

05:15.875 --> 05:18.041
WELL, I RECENTLY
MADE THE DECISION.

05:18.041 --> 05:19.166
I WAS HOPING THAT YOU
WOULD BE PSYCHED FOR ME.

05:19.166 --> 05:21.125
I AM  PSYCHED FOR YOU.

05:21.125 --> 05:23.959
IT'S AN INCREDIBLE JOB.

05:23.959 --> 05:25.417
I THINK YOU'LL
BE GREAT AT IT.

05:27.583 --> 05:31.291
BUT SUDDENLY,
THIS TACIT LITTLE ISSUE
THAT'S BEEN

05:31.291 --> 05:32.667
FLOATING IN THE BACK
OF BOTH OF OUR MINDS

05:32.667 --> 05:33.875
HAS BECOME VERY REAL.

05:33.875 --> 05:35.208
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
TALK ABOUT IT EVENTUALLY--

05:35.208 --> 05:39.667
"IT" REFERRING TO
THE POTENTIAL CONTINENT
BETWEEN US.

05:41.667 --> 05:42.875
OK.

05:42.875 --> 05:46.166
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT LONG DISTANCE
RELATIONSHIPS?

05:46.166 --> 05:50.250
HISTORICALLY, THEY
DON'T HAVE THE BEST
TRACK RECORD, BUT--

05:50.250 --> 05:51.834
BUT WE COULD BE
THAT ONE COUPLE.

05:51.834 --> 05:53.291
ABSOLUTELY.

05:54.291 --> 05:55.625
ONE OF US COULD
ALSO JOIN THE OTHER.

06:00.834 --> 06:03.291
HOW COULD I ASK YOU
TO COME TO CALIFORNIA?

06:03.291 --> 06:05.625
HOW COULD I ASK YOU
TO COME TO BOSTON?

06:07.208 --> 06:09.667
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE? WE'RE--

06:09.667 --> 06:12.583
LAST WEEK, WE'RE DECLARING
OUR LOVE FOR EACH OTHER.

06:12.583 --> 06:14.125
NOW IT SOUNDS LIKE
WE'RE BREAKING UP.

06:14.125 --> 06:17.166
WELL, I JUST THINK WE'RE
DEALING WITH REALITY.

06:17.166 --> 06:18.542
WHICH IS WHAT?

06:18.542 --> 06:23.708
RIGHT NOW IT'S DINNER
BY CANDLELIGHT

06:23.708 --> 06:26.291
WITH THE MAN I LOVE.

06:34.667 --> 06:37.375
YOU'RE PRETTY GOOD AT THIS
TEACHING THING, MR. McPHEE.

06:37.375 --> 06:38.667
WELL, I HAVE TO SAY,
I KIND OF ENJOY IT.

06:38.667 --> 06:40.834
NOW IF WE CAN JUST GET YOU
TO SHOW UP ON TIME.

06:40.834 --> 06:43.542
POINT TAKEN, PAL,
WHICH IS WHY YOU'RE
LEAVING EARLY.

06:43.542 --> 06:45.250
OH, COME ON.
THAT'S NOT NECESSARY.

06:45.250 --> 06:46.291
YEAH, IT IS.

06:46.291 --> 06:47.667
I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF
YOUR GRIEF FOR ONE DAY,

06:47.667 --> 06:49.166
SO I'LL STAY WITH WILL
AND MAKE SURE HIS MOM
PICKS HIM UP.

06:49.166 --> 06:51.250
I'LL PAY MY PENANCE.

06:51.250 --> 06:52.417
YOU SURE?

06:52.417 --> 06:53.417
GO.

06:53.417 --> 06:55.208
YOU SURE YOU KNOW
HOW TO LOCK UP AFTER--

06:55.208 --> 06:56.417
WHY ARE YOU STILL HERE?

06:56.417 --> 06:58.250
OK. GOOD NIGHT, JACK.
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

06:58.250 --> 07:01.166
ALL RIGHT. LATER, TOBEY.

07:01.166 --> 07:04.458
WILL, GIVE ME A HAND
HERE WITH THOSE, PLEASE.

07:11.917 --> 07:13.667
OOH.

07:16.250 --> 07:17.708
WHOO!

07:17.708 --> 07:19.000
COLD NIGHT.

07:19.000 --> 07:20.750
BUSES RUN LATE.

07:24.583 --> 07:26.583
[CAR DOOR SLAMS]

07:28.834 --> 07:30.583
I'M REALLY SORRY
TO COME BY SO LATE.

07:30.583 --> 07:32.083
IT'S COOL.
DAWSON JUST LEFT.

07:32.083 --> 07:33.625
LOOK, I REALLY NEED
TO TALK TO PACEY.

07:33.625 --> 07:35.125
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHEN HE'S GONNA BE BACK
FROM HIS FISHING TRIP?

07:35.125 --> 07:40.250
NO, I DON'T, BUT I'M SURE
HE'LL CALL YOU AS SOON
AS HE GETS BACK.

07:41.208 --> 07:43.333
THERE'S SOMETHING
WRONG, ISN'T THERE?

07:43.333 --> 07:45.959
I MEAN, THIS ISN'T
LIKE PACEY.

07:45.959 --> 07:47.792
GRETCHEN,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

07:47.792 --> 07:50.083
YOU KNOW, I TOLD HIM
I WOULDN'T DO THIS ANYMORE,

07:50.083 --> 07:51.875
AND I WON'T.

07:52.875 --> 07:53.917
WHAT?

07:53.917 --> 07:56.000
LYING.

07:56.000 --> 07:57.875
IT'S THE WORST THING
FOR EVERYONE.

07:57.875 --> 08:02.041
PACEY ISN'T ON
A FISHING TRIP, IS HE?

08:02.041 --> 08:05.750
PACEY GOT ARRESTED FOR
PUBLIC DRUNKENNESS WHILE
YOU WERE IN NEW YORK.

08:05.750 --> 08:08.375
DOUG GOT THE CHARGES
DROPPED, AND THEN
HE TOOK HIM CAMPING

08:08.375 --> 08:10.458
TO TRY TO TALK
SOME SENSE INTO HIM.

08:11.959 --> 08:12.875
OH, MY GOD.

08:12.875 --> 08:15.125
THIS IS AN INTENSE TIME.

08:15.125 --> 08:16.625
WE'RE ALL PLANNING
OUR FUTURES,

08:16.625 --> 08:18.458
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO WITH
THE REST OF OUR LIVES,

08:18.458 --> 08:21.000
BUT IF WE CAN'T
PUT ALL THAT ASIDE

08:21.000 --> 08:22.667
AND TRY TO DO
EVERYTHING POSSIBLE

08:22.667 --> 08:24.834
TO MAKE PACEY'S LIFE
EASIER RIGHT NOW,

08:24.834 --> 08:26.834
HE MIGHT NOT
HAVE MUCH OF ONE.

08:26.834 --> 08:29.125
HE'S IN A LOT OF PAIN,

08:29.125 --> 08:31.333
SO YOU HAVE TO
PROMISE ME THAT YOU
WON'T DO ANYTHING

08:31.333 --> 08:32.375
TO PUT ANY ADDITIONAL
PRESSURE ON HIM
RIGHT NOW, OK?

08:32.375 --> 08:35.000
I MEAN, CAN YOU DO THAT?

08:35.000 --> 08:38.833
DO YOU OR DO YOU NOT
KNOW HOW I CAN GET
IN TOUCH WITH HIM?

08:38.833 --> 08:40.332
DID YOU JUST HEAR
WHAT I SAID?

08:40.332 --> 08:42.041
NO. I CAN'T PROMISE
YOU THAT, GRETCHEN.

08:42.041 --> 08:43.332
HOW COULD YOU POSSIBLY
BE THAT SELFISH?

08:45.500 --> 08:46.750
I'M LATE.

08:54.583 --> 08:56.917
JOEY, I'M SO SORRY.
I HAD NO IDEA.

08:58.208 --> 08:59.917
IT'S OK.
I'M FINE, THANK YOU.

08:59.917 --> 09:01.000
[SNIFFS]

09:01.000 --> 09:02.583
DID YOU CONFIRM
THAT YOU'RE PREGNANT?

09:02.583 --> 09:04.250
NO. I REALLY JUST NEED
TO TALK TO MY BOYFRIEND,

09:04.250 --> 09:05.708
SO IF THERE'S ANY WAY
THAT YOU CAN GET
IN TOUCH WITH HIM--

09:05.708 --> 09:07.583
AS SOON AS THEY
GET BACK HERE
OR IF THEY CALL IN,

09:07.583 --> 09:10.959
I PROMISE TO MAKE
SURE THAT PACEY GETS
IN TOUCH WITH YOU.

09:10.959 --> 09:12.542
THANK YOU.

09:12.542 --> 09:15.542
JOEY, I KNOW THAT
THINGS SEEM CONFUSING

09:15.542 --> 09:17.041
AND FRIGHTENING,

09:17.041 --> 09:19.458
BUT YOU HAVE TO
FIND THE COURAGE
TO TAKE THE TEST,

09:19.458 --> 09:20.834
AND THAT WAY, YOU CAN
CONSIDER YOUR OPTIONS.

09:20.834 --> 09:21.708
JOEY!

09:21.708 --> 09:26.000
I'M FINE.
I CAN HANDLE THIS.

09:26.000 --> 09:28.041
LOOK, IF YOU CHANGE
YOUR MIND, YOU CAN
ALWAYS COME BACK HERE...

09:28.041 --> 09:29.667
ANY TIME.

09:33.625 --> 09:38.708
OH, YOU GUYS,
I THOUGHT I MADE YOU
PROMISE--NO GIFTS.

09:38.708 --> 09:40.542
ASKING LADIES
NOT TO BRING GIFTS
TO A SHOWER

09:40.542 --> 09:43.417
IS LIKE ASKING THE
SUN NOT TO SHINE,

09:43.417 --> 09:46.417
BIRDS NOT TO SING.

09:46.417 --> 09:48.500
GOOD LORD. GIVE THIS
WOMAN A BALL OF YARN
AND SOME KNITTING NEEDLES,

09:48.500 --> 09:49.875
YOU'LL BE AMAZED WHAT
SHE CAN COME UP WITH.

09:49.875 --> 09:52.250
OH, EXCUSE ME.
MY KITCHEN'S CALLING.

09:52.250 --> 09:55.625
OH, HI, HONEY.

09:58.083 --> 10:01.083
DAWSON, WHY ISN'T
YOUR MOM, LIKE, ON THE COUCH
WITH HER FEET UP?

10:01.083 --> 10:02.291
OH, SHE'S NOT INTERESTED.

10:02.291 --> 10:04.208
SHE'S COOKING,
SHE'S CLEANING,
SHE'S RELENTLESS.

10:04.208 --> 10:05.750
NESTING INSTINCT.

10:05.750 --> 10:07.166
DO YOU WANT
SOME LAUNDRY DONE?
YOU COULD MAKE HER DAY.

10:07.166 --> 10:09.083
COME ON.

10:09.083 --> 10:10.083
HEY.

10:10.083 --> 10:14.500
HEY.

10:14.500 --> 10:15.583
I WENT TO THE BOOKSTORE
THIS MORNING

10:15.583 --> 10:17.667
AND LOOKED AT
SOME MAGAZINES--

10:17.667 --> 10:20.375
ONCE CERTAIN CITY
MAGAZINE IN PARTICULAR.

10:20.375 --> 10:21.417
IT'S A GREAT READ.

10:21.417 --> 10:22.875
I SPENT THE WHOLE
MORNING TRYING TO PACK,

10:22.875 --> 10:26.041
YOU KNOW,
AND I HAVE TO ADMIT,
I'M A LITTLE NERVOUS.

10:26.041 --> 10:28.250
I MEAN, THE ONLY REAL
JOB INTERVIEW I EVER HAD
WAS WITH YOUR MOTHER.

10:28.750 --> 10:30.208
MOM, I GOT IT.

10:30.208 --> 10:31.375
OH, THANKS, HONEY.

10:31.375 --> 10:33.208
AH! HI, GRETCH.
HI.

10:33.208 --> 10:34.166
HEY.

10:34.166 --> 10:35.208
HI, JOEY.

10:35.208 --> 10:37.083
HOW YOU DOIN'?

10:37.083 --> 10:38.417
FINE.

10:38.417 --> 10:40.083
LOOK, JOEY, IF YOU NEED
ANYTHING AT ALL, I'M HERE.

10:40.083 --> 10:43.917
WOULD YOU PLEASE
TELL MY SISTER TO GET
A LIFE OF HER OWN?

10:43.917 --> 10:45.166
YOUR BROTHER GOES FISHING,
AND, I SWEAR,

10:45.166 --> 10:46.291
SHE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH HERSELF.

10:46.291 --> 10:49.291
OH, JOEY!

10:49.291 --> 10:51.333
HI.
HI.

10:51.333 --> 10:52.166
OH, I HAVEN'T
SEEN YOU IN SO LONG.
HOW ARE YOU?

10:52.166 --> 10:53.208
NEVER BETTER.

10:53.208 --> 10:56.542
OH!

10:56.542 --> 11:00.458
OK! EVERYBODY,
LET'S GET STARTED.

11:00.458 --> 11:01.834
ARE YOU STAYING?

11:01.834 --> 11:03.041
I...

11:03.041 --> 11:04.500
TRADITION IS VERY CLEAR
ON THIS MATTER.

11:04.500 --> 11:05.625
NO MEN AT SHOWERS.

11:05.625 --> 11:08.000
WELL, IN CASE YOU
HAVEN'T NOTICED,

11:08.000 --> 11:10.208
WE'RE KIND OF
A NON-TRADITIONAL
HOUSEHOLD.

11:10.208 --> 11:11.583
THAT'S OK.
DAD AND I WILL LEAVE

11:11.583 --> 11:13.708
AND LET YOU WOMEN DO
WHATEVER IT IS YOU DO
AT THESE THINGS.

11:13.708 --> 11:15.542
COME ON, DAWSON.

11:15.542 --> 11:17.458
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE
BEFORE THE VAGINA
MONOLOGUES  START.

11:17.458 --> 11:19.250
OH!
OH!

11:23.667 --> 11:24.750
WILL, WHERE'S TOBEY?

11:24.750 --> 11:25.875
I DON'T KNOW.

11:25.875 --> 11:28.959
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN HIM,
HEARD FROM HIM, ANYTHING?

11:28.959 --> 11:29.542
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

11:29.542 --> 11:31.834
FRANK, GET OFF THAT!

11:36.375 --> 11:38.834
IT'S MOVING.
IT'S ACTUALLY MOVING.

11:38.834 --> 11:39.834
WHERE DID YOU
LEARN THIS?

11:39.834 --> 11:43.333
GENERATIONS OF WOMEN
HAVE DONE THIS.

11:43.333 --> 11:46.667
IT WAS THE ULTRASOUND
OF THE MIDDLE AGES.

11:46.667 --> 11:49.250
SO WHAT IS IT?

11:49.250 --> 11:52.041
A BOY OR A GIRL?

11:52.041 --> 11:54.583
IT'S JUST WHAT YOU WANT.

11:54.583 --> 11:57.834
[LAUGHS]

11:57.834 --> 12:00.542
Bessie:
I'D LIKE TO GO FIRST.

12:00.542 --> 12:02.333
THESE ARE FROM
BODIE AND ME.

12:02.333 --> 12:03.417
SOPHIE.

12:03.417 --> 12:05.500
THAT'S AN ADORABLE NAME.

12:05.500 --> 12:07.750
IT MEANS "WISE."

12:07.750 --> 12:08.333
THAT'S WHAT WE WERE
GONNA NAME ALEXANDER
IF HE WAS A GIRL.

12:08.333 --> 12:10.542
HMM. SOPHIE LEERY.

12:10.542 --> 12:13.500
IF YOU HAVE A BOY...

12:13.500 --> 12:15.208
SATCHEL?

12:15.208 --> 12:16.750
Bessie:
HE PLAYED BASEBALL.

12:16.750 --> 12:18.750
BODIE SWORE
MITCH WOULD LOVE IT.

12:18.750 --> 12:20.000
[LADIES LAUGH]

12:22.375 --> 12:24.208
HERE WE GO.

12:24.208 --> 12:25.208
[LAUGHS]

12:25.208 --> 12:27.375
WHAT?

12:27.375 --> 12:28.125
[LAUGHS]

12:28.125 --> 12:30.500
SORRY. I DON'T
PICTURE YOU

12:30.500 --> 12:33.458
AS A STOGIE-SMOKING
KIND OF DAD.

12:33.458 --> 12:36.875
WELL, EVIDENTLY,
IT'S WHAT YOU'RE
SUPPOSED TO DO

12:36.875 --> 12:37.959
AT A TIME LIKE THIS.

12:37.959 --> 12:39.417
ACCORDING TO WHO,
LARRY FLYNT?

12:39.417 --> 12:40.667
ACCORDING TO MR. KASDAN.

12:40.667 --> 12:42.208
IT WAS HIS GIFT.

12:42.208 --> 12:44.417
I TOLD HIM
I'D DO THIS WITH YOU.

12:44.417 --> 12:46.333
I DID NOT, HOWEVER,
PROMISE HIM

12:46.333 --> 12:49.959
THAT WE WOULD
ACTUALLY LIGHT
THESE DEADLY THINGS.

12:55.417 --> 12:56.750
[LADIES LAUGH]

12:56.750 --> 13:01.083
SO, YOU THINK
ANY OF THE NAMES

13:01.083 --> 13:02.959
THEY'RE KICKIN'
AROUND DOWN
THERE'LL STICK?

13:02.959 --> 13:05.959
I WONDER IF
OUR INABILITY
TO DECIDE ON A NAME

13:05.959 --> 13:07.458
MEANS THAT WE
AREN'T REALLY DEALING

13:07.458 --> 13:10.250
WITH WHAT'S ABOUT TO
HAPPEN IN OUR LIVES.

13:10.250 --> 13:11.625
YEAH, BUT
THE GOOD NEWS IS,

13:11.625 --> 13:13.708
YOU GUYS HAVE
HAD A BABY BEFORE,

13:13.708 --> 13:14.792
SO YOU KNOW
WHAT TO EXPECT, RIGHT?

13:14.792 --> 13:17.291
WANT TO KNOW THE TRUTH?

13:17.291 --> 13:21.792
HAVING A NEWBORN
IN YOUR LIFE IS PURE,
UNADULTERATED HELL.

13:21.792 --> 13:22.417
IT CAN'T BE THAT BAD.

13:22.417 --> 13:25.000
OH, BUT IT IS,

13:25.000 --> 13:28.125
UNLESS YOU
HAVE A BREAST.

13:28.125 --> 13:32.917
A MAN DOESN'T REALLY
LOVE A BABY THE WAY
A WOMAN DOES--

13:32.917 --> 13:33.959
NOT AT FIRST.

13:33.959 --> 13:37.125
A MAN LOVES THE IDEA
OF A BABY.

13:38.291 --> 13:38.959
THAT CHANGES, RIGHT?

13:40.375 --> 13:42.834
ONE NIGHT,

13:42.834 --> 13:46.500
YOU'RE STANDING
IN A DARK ROOM,

13:46.500 --> 13:47.625
EXHAUSTED,

13:47.625 --> 13:50.125
REACHING FOR DIAPERS

13:50.125 --> 13:53.291
AND ANSWERS ON A SHELF
YOU CAN'T SEE,

13:53.291 --> 13:58.041
AND THIS LITTLE PERSON
CALLS OUT TO YOU.

13:59.667 --> 14:01.291
"DADDY."

14:03.834 --> 14:05.166
THAT'S WHEN YOU GET IT.

14:07.500 --> 14:11.834
YOU FEEL YOUR HEART
EXPAND IN A WAY

14:11.834 --> 14:13.250
YOU NEVER KNEW
WAS POSSIBLE,

14:13.250 --> 14:16.750
AND YOU LOVE THIS
LITTLE PERSON SO MUCH...

14:17.750 --> 14:20.792
THAT YOU ACTUALLY ACHE.

14:28.792 --> 14:31.834
I CAN'T EXPLAIN IT
ANY BETTER.

14:32.834 --> 14:35.125
I THINK THE REASON
YOU GUYS ARE WAITING

14:35.125 --> 14:37.792
IS BECAUSE YOU DON'T
WANT TO JUST SLAP
A NAME ON THIS IDEA.

14:37.792 --> 14:39.208
I THINK YOU
WANT TO GET A SENSE

14:39.208 --> 14:42.542
OF WHO THIS NEW MEMBER
OF OUR FAMILY IS,

14:42.542 --> 14:46.417
AND I THINK WHEN YOU
MEET HIM, YOU'LL KNOW.

14:50.250 --> 14:52.458
YOU'RE A PRETTY
SMART KID, DAWSON.

14:52.458 --> 14:54.667
HA HA HA!

14:55.375 --> 14:57.875
IF I WERE TO
HAVE A GIRL,

14:57.875 --> 14:58.875
I THINK I'D
NAME HER EMMA.

14:58.875 --> 15:03.041
AND FOR A BOY,
MAYBE JACKSON?

15:03.041 --> 15:04.875
JACKSON POLLOCK.

15:04.875 --> 15:05.583
MADE A
BEAUTIFUL MESS.

15:05.583 --> 15:08.125
[LADIES LAUGH]

15:08.125 --> 15:10.083
MY FAVORITE BOYS' NAME--KURT.

15:10.083 --> 15:10.750
STRONG NAME.

15:10.750 --> 15:12.542
FOR KURT DONALD COBAIN.

15:12.542 --> 15:13.834
HA HA HA!

15:13.834 --> 15:15.750
Gretchen: AND MY FAVORITE
GIRLS' NAME--

15:15.750 --> 15:17.083
ISABELLA,

15:17.083 --> 15:18.834
AFTER A STORY
THAT MY GRANDMOTHER
USED TO TELL ME

15:18.834 --> 15:19.917
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE GIRL.

15:19.917 --> 15:22.333
THERE ARE MANY FLOWERS
IN THE GARDEN,

15:22.333 --> 15:25.333
BUT THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
WILL ALWAYS BE ROSE.

15:25.333 --> 15:27.583
ROSE LEERY.

15:27.583 --> 15:31.708
AND FOR A BOY, THOMAS,

15:31.708 --> 15:35.667
FOR SOMEONE I KNEW
A LONG TIME AGO.

15:39.417 --> 15:43.417
GRETCHEN'S PROBABLY
GONNA TAKE A JOB
IN BOSTON.

15:43.417 --> 15:45.583
YOU THINK
IT'S A REACTION

15:45.583 --> 15:46.917
TO YOU
GETTING INTO USC?

15:46.917 --> 15:48.250
A WAY OF
PROTECTING HERSELF?

15:49.291 --> 15:50.750
I DON'T KNOW.

15:50.750 --> 15:53.792
I MEAN, I NEVER
EXPECTED HER TO
FOLLOW ME TO CALIFORNIA,

15:53.792 --> 15:56.250
AND IT'S A GREAT
OPPORTUNITY.

15:56.250 --> 15:58.291
I'M REALLY HAPPY
FOR HER, BUT--

15:58.291 --> 16:00.208
WELL, JUST REMEMBER,
A COUPLE YEARS AGO,

16:00.208 --> 16:01.083
YOUR MOTHER AND I
GOT A DIVORCE.

16:01.083 --> 16:04.208
NOW WE'RE MORE
IN LOVE THAN EVER.

16:04.208 --> 16:08.917
SO YOU'RE SAYING
MAYBE EVEN IF WE BREAK UP,

16:08.917 --> 16:11.708
WE'RE STILL DESTINED
TO BE TOGETHER?

16:11.708 --> 16:14.458
I'M SAYING YOU HAVE TO
FOLLOW YOUR OWN PATH,

16:14.458 --> 16:16.583
BECAUSE WITH EVERYTHING
ELSE IN THIS LIFE,

16:16.583 --> 16:17.166
YOU JUST NEVER KNOW.

16:20.333 --> 16:22.291
LOOK AT YOU AND JOEY.

16:22.291 --> 16:23.667
HEH.

16:27.917 --> 16:31.375
WELL, I WAS UP
ALL NIGHT LAST NIGHT,

16:31.375 --> 16:33.041
AND I COULDN'T
THINK OF A NAME,

16:33.041 --> 16:35.750
BUT I BROUGHT YOU
THIS INSTEAD.

16:35.750 --> 16:38.125
I THINK IT EMBODIES
EVERYTHING THAT
A NAME SHOULD.

16:38.875 --> 16:41.583
IT USED TO BELONG TO DAWSON,

16:41.583 --> 16:44.166
AND, AT SOME POINT,
I'M SURE HIS LITTLE
BROTHER OR SISTER

16:44.166 --> 16:46.375
WILL LIKE TO WEAR IT.

16:46.375 --> 16:49.500
IT'S GETTING HARDER TO
TELL WHAT'S RIGHT ANYMORE,

16:49.500 --> 16:50.500
SO I HOPE YOU LIKE IT.

16:50.500 --> 16:53.083
WELL, OF COURSE IT'S OK,
HONEY. THANK YOU.

16:53.083 --> 16:56.583
I'M SURE DAWSON WILL BE
AS TOUCHED AS I AM.

17:00.125 --> 17:02.375
AND THANK ALL OF YOU.

17:02.375 --> 17:06.125
YOU HAVE GIVEN ME
SO MUCH TO THINK ABOUT
DURING THIS LABOR

17:06.125 --> 17:08.500
INSTEAD OF
MY CONTRACTIONS.

17:08.500 --> 17:09.625
WELL, YOU CAN BE THANKFUL
THAT YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE

17:09.625 --> 17:12.666
DELIVERING THE BABY IN
THE MIDDLE OF A HURRICANE.

17:12.666 --> 17:13.791
LET'S HOPE NOT.

17:13.791 --> 17:16.458
AS BAD AS THAT WAS,
IT WASN'T NEAR AS DIFFICULT

17:16.458 --> 17:18.541
AS WHAT I SAW
MY MOTHER GO THROUGH.

17:18.541 --> 17:20.750
LILLIAN WAS
AN AMAZING WOMAN.

17:20.750 --> 17:23.375
I LOVED HER SO MUCH.

17:23.375 --> 17:25.416
34 HOURS AFTER
HER WATER BROKE,

17:25.416 --> 17:27.040
THE BABY STILL
HADN'T APPEARED.

17:27.040 --> 17:29.208
SO, WHAT MADE YOU FINALLY
DECIDE TO COME OUT AND
MAKE YOUR GRAND ENTRANCE?

17:29.208 --> 17:32.208
MY MOTHER STARTED
CALLING OUT HER NAME--

17:32.208 --> 17:33.375
"JOSEPHINE! JOSEPHINE!

17:33.375 --> 17:35.041
EVERYONE'S
WAITING TO MEET YOU,"

17:35.041 --> 17:37.000
AND THERE SHE WAS.

17:37.000 --> 17:40.166
THIS MASS OF WET,
CHOCOLATE HAIR,

17:40.166 --> 17:43.166
THESE CURIOUS,
SAUCER EYES,

17:43.166 --> 17:46.208
AND A POUT WE
ALL KNOW WAY TOO WELL.

17:49.041 --> 17:50.375
EXCUSE ME.

17:57.083 --> 17:58.458
[KNOCKS]

17:58.458 --> 17:59.708
Tobey: GO AWAY.

17:59.708 --> 18:01.000
YOU ALL RIGHT?

18:01.000 --> 18:03.959
Tobey: I'VE
GOT THE FLU.

18:03.959 --> 18:06.250
YOU DON'T SOUND SICK.

18:06.250 --> 18:07.959
[COUGHS] IT'S BAD.

18:07.959 --> 18:09.250
I'M HIGHLY
CONTAGIOUS.

18:09.250 --> 18:10.750
GO AWAY.

18:10.750 --> 18:12.750
I JUST HAD THE FLU.

18:12.750 --> 18:15.917
THIS IS A DIFFERENT
STRAIN--STRAIN "D."

18:15.917 --> 18:17.417
YOU HAVEN'T
HAD THIS. [COUGHS]

18:17.417 --> 18:20.583
COME ON, TOBEY.
OPEN UP.

18:20.583 --> 18:22.417
COME ON, MAN.

18:24.583 --> 18:26.750
SOME FLU.

18:26.750 --> 18:29.792
YEAH. DON'T FREAK.

18:29.792 --> 18:31.083
IT ONLY HURTS
WHEN I BLINK.

18:31.083 --> 18:32.959
WHAT HAPPENED?

18:32.959 --> 18:36.208
I HAD A DIVERGENCE
OF OPINION

18:36.208 --> 18:37.417
ON HOW A COUPLE OF
LOCAL ENTREPRENEURS

18:37.417 --> 18:40.875
SHOULD PAY FOR
THEIR CRACK, AND I
LOST THE DISPUTE.

18:40.875 --> 18:42.041
SO YOU GOT MUGGED.

18:42.041 --> 18:42.875
YEAH.

18:42.875 --> 18:43.875
NOW, LOOK,
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

18:43.875 --> 18:46.417
MY ICE PACK
IS THAWING.

18:46.417 --> 18:47.000
HEH.

18:47.000 --> 18:49.375
DID YOU REPORT IT?

18:49.375 --> 18:51.875
LOOK, IT WAS
A MUGGING. THEY
GOT 12 BUCKS.

18:51.875 --> 18:52.917
IT'S NOT WORTH
THE TROUBLE.

18:52.917 --> 18:54.041
COME ON.
I DON'T WANT TO
TALK ABOUT IT.

18:54.041 --> 18:55.625
IT'LL TAKE 10 MINUTES.
WE JUST GO TO THE COPS--

18:55.625 --> 18:56.667
WHAT AM I
GONNA TELL 'EM?

18:56.667 --> 18:58.291
THAT I FRIGHTEN
SOME PEOPLE,

18:58.291 --> 18:58.917
SO THEY BEAT
THE CRAP OUT OF ME?

18:58.917 --> 18:59.834
JUST GO HOME, JACK.

18:59.834 --> 19:01.667
WHOA, WHOA. TOBE--TOBEY!

19:01.667 --> 19:03.083
[SLAM]

19:03.083 --> 19:05.792
WHAT IS GOING ON
WITH YOU?

19:05.792 --> 19:07.834
IS IT SUDDENLY
INAPPROPRIATE OR IMMORAL

19:07.834 --> 19:08.458
TO GET
A LITTLE EMOTIONAL

19:08.458 --> 19:09.959
AT A BABY SHOWER?

19:09.959 --> 19:11.375
YOU'RE MORE
THAN EMOTIONAL.
YOU'RE NEUROTIC.

19:11.375 --> 19:13.000
YOU'RE OBSESSED WITH
FINDING YOUR BOYFRIEND.

19:13.000 --> 19:13.834
YOU'RE CREEPED OUT
BEING HERE.

19:13.834 --> 19:15.208
EVERY TIME GALE
LOOKS AT YOU,

19:15.208 --> 19:16.500
YOU LOOK
THE OTHER WAY.

19:16.500 --> 19:18.041
IF I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WEREN'T HAVING SEX,

19:18.041 --> 19:20.083
I'D...

19:20.792 --> 19:22.125
JOEY.

19:22.125 --> 19:24.458
CAN YOU JUST
LEAVE ME ALONE?

19:24.458 --> 19:27.125
ARE YOU PREGNANT?

19:27.125 --> 19:29.166
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

19:29.166 --> 19:30.333
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.
WHAT HAPPENED?

19:30.333 --> 19:33.291
I'M NOT HAVING
THIS CONVERSATION WITH YOU.

19:33.291 --> 19:34.500
HEY, YOU BETTER
WATCH IT,

19:34.500 --> 19:36.750
BECAUSE IF SOMETHING
IS WRONG, YOU'RE
GONNA NEED ME.

19:36.750 --> 19:40.000
WHY, SO I CAN SIT
THROUGH ANOTHER SERIES
OF ENDLESS LECTURES?

19:40.000 --> 19:41.291
SO YOU CAN STRAIGHTEN
OUT YOUR LIFE.

19:41.291 --> 19:44.208
OH, AND HAVE ONE
MORE LIKE YOURS.

19:44.208 --> 19:45.542
[LAUGHS]

19:45.542 --> 19:46.834
YOU THINK YOU'RE
BETTER THAN ME?

19:46.834 --> 19:48.291
LOOK AT YOU. YOU'RE
JUST LIKE MOM.
YOU'RE JUST LIKE ME.

19:48.291 --> 19:51.834
NO, I'M NOT, BECAUSE
I ASSURE YOU, BESSIE,

19:51.834 --> 19:54.291
THAT NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,
MY LIFE WILL BE DIFFERENT.

19:54.291 --> 19:55.333
YOU SAID THAT RIGHT,

19:55.333 --> 19:56.417
BECAUSE AT LEAST I HAVE
SOMEONE IN MY LIFE

19:56.417 --> 19:57.834
WHO KNOWS HOW TO
TAKE CARE HIMSELF,

19:57.834 --> 19:59.333
NOT TO MENTION
A FAMILY. DO YOU?

19:59.333 --> 20:01.834
Gale: SOMEBODY
GET MY JACKET!

20:01.834 --> 20:03.041
Grams: GOT IT.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

20:03.041 --> 20:04.500
GALE IS IN LABOR.

20:10.583 --> 20:11.542
WELL, I GOT TO HAND IT
TO YOU, MOM.

20:11.542 --> 20:13.708
THAT IS THE FASTEST WAY
TO END A PARTY

20:13.708 --> 20:15.542
AND CLEAR OUT THE HOUSE
I'VE EVER SEEN.

20:15.542 --> 20:16.583
GOING INTO LABOR.

20:16.583 --> 20:18.542
I'LL HAVE
TO REMEMBER THAT ONE.

20:18.542 --> 20:19.708
HOW ARE YOU
FEELING, GALE?

20:19.708 --> 20:20.125
I WANT DRUGS.

20:20.125 --> 20:21.667
SO DO I.

20:21.667 --> 20:23.125
WE'LL SEE WHAT
WE CAN DO.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.041
HOWDY, STRANGER.

20:29.041 --> 20:29.750
WHAT, ARE YOU CHURNING
BUTTER NOW, TOO?

20:29.750 --> 20:31.667
[LAUGHS]

20:31.667 --> 20:33.625
GRAMS HAS THE NEEDLES
WORKING IN OVERDRIVE

20:33.625 --> 20:35.041
FOR GALE'S BABY.

20:35.041 --> 20:36.625
THERE'S SOMETHING
KIND OF MEDITATIVE

20:36.625 --> 20:38.375
AND THERAPEUTIC
ABOUT IT, TOO.

20:38.375 --> 20:41.625
SO, WHAT BRINGS YOU
TO THESE PARTS?

20:41.625 --> 20:42.166
[SIGHS]

20:42.166 --> 20:44.542
JUST WANDERING.

20:44.542 --> 20:45.625
THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE DO
IN THESE KINDS OF TOWNS.

20:45.625 --> 20:47.875
THEY JUST WANDER OVER
TO THEIR FRIENDS' HOMES

20:47.875 --> 20:51.000
AND...PONDER
THEIR TRIVIAL PROBLEMS.

20:51.000 --> 20:51.917
[LAUGHS]

20:51.917 --> 20:54.000
TELL ME TALES
OF YOUR TRIVIAL WOES.

20:54.917 --> 20:56.250
WOE IS TOBEY.

20:56.250 --> 20:59.375
THAT BOY IS IN LOVE.

20:59.375 --> 21:01.583
THAT BOY IS
ON CRUTCHES.

21:01.583 --> 21:03.083
CRUTCHES?

21:03.083 --> 21:03.583
SERIOUSLY?
WHAT HAPPENED?

21:05.291 --> 21:06.667
HE SAYS HE GOT ROBBED.

21:06.667 --> 21:08.583
YOU KNOW,
IF I GOT ROBBED,
I'D BE FURIOUS.

21:08.583 --> 21:09.917
I'D WANT TO REPORT IT,
I'D WANT TO DO SOMETHING.

21:09.917 --> 21:12.083
YEAH, ME, TOO.

21:12.083 --> 21:14.792
WELL, HE JUST WANTS
TO BE LEFT ALONE.

21:14.792 --> 21:17.417
I THINK HE GOT ATTACKED
'CAUSE HE'S GAY.

21:17.417 --> 21:19.708
OH, GOD.

21:19.708 --> 21:21.208
YOU THINK I'M
BEING PARANOID?

21:21.208 --> 21:22.083
NO.

21:22.083 --> 21:24.750
NO. PARANOID IS
HEALTHY. TRUST ME.

21:24.750 --> 21:26.166
HE WAS THE GUY ON TOP
OF THE SOAP BOX

21:26.166 --> 21:27.250
WHEN WE FIRST MET HIM.

21:27.250 --> 21:29.083
HE WAS CARRYING ON
ABOUT TAKING ACTION.

21:29.083 --> 21:31.625
SO WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO?

21:31.625 --> 21:32.834
I--I DON'T KNOW.

21:32.834 --> 21:33.625
I MEAN, I TRIED
TO TALK TO HIM.

21:33.625 --> 21:35.875
HE DOESN'T
WANT ANY HELP.

21:35.875 --> 21:36.750
WHAT, AND YOU'RE JUST
GONNA LEAVE IT AT THAT?

21:36.750 --> 21:38.667
YEAH. WHAT DO YOU
WANT ME TO DO?

21:38.667 --> 21:40.458
I MEAN, IT'S REALLY
NONE OF MY BUSINESS.

21:40.458 --> 21:41.375
JACK...

21:41.375 --> 21:43.583
IF I GOT ATTACKED,
WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

21:43.583 --> 21:44.667
THAT'S NOT
THE SAME THING.

21:44.667 --> 21:46.542
NO, THE ONLY DIFFERENCE
IS THAT IN THIS CASE,

21:46.542 --> 21:47.959
YOU'RE EXACTLY LIKE
THE VICTIM.

21:56.959 --> 21:59.333
FOR MY DAD. HE'S NERVOUS
ABOUT BRINGING A NEWBORN

21:59.333 --> 22:00.375
INTO HIS LIFE.

22:00.375 --> 22:01.291
[LAUGHS]

22:01.291 --> 22:02.500
WELL, IT CHANGES
EVERYTHING.

22:02.500 --> 22:04.708
CONSISTENTLY PUTTING
SOMEBODY ELSE'S WANTS

22:04.708 --> 22:06.458
AND NEEDS
BEFORE YOUR OWN.

22:06.458 --> 22:09.166
I THINK THAT'S WHAT FINALLY
MAKES US A GROWNUP.

22:09.166 --> 22:10.542
WONDER WHAT THAT
SAYS ABOUT US.

22:13.375 --> 22:16.125
I THINK WE CONSIDER EACH
OTHER'S NEEDS, DAWSON.

22:17.125 --> 22:19.750
YEAH, UP TO A POINT.

22:19.750 --> 22:21.792
AND THEN, YOU KNOW, WE HAVE
TO THINK ABOUT OURSELVES.

22:21.792 --> 22:22.667
DO YOU THINK IT
SHOULD BE DIFFERENT

22:22.667 --> 22:24.667
AT THIS TIME
IN OUR LIVES?

22:24.667 --> 22:25.583
I...

22:25.583 --> 22:28.792
I--I DON'T KNOW.

22:28.792 --> 22:31.083
ALL I KNOW IS THAT THERE'S
THIS STUPID PART OF ME

22:31.083 --> 22:32.792
THAT JUST WANTS TO BEG YOU
TO COME WITH ME.

22:32.792 --> 22:35.125
AND THE OTHER PART
OF YOU?

22:36.458 --> 22:39.166
THE OTHER PART
OF ME IS SMARTER...

22:39.166 --> 22:41.208
AND KNOWS THAT YOU HAVE
TO LET PEOPLE GO.

22:49.250 --> 22:50.125
THE TIMING SUCKS.

22:50.125 --> 22:52.500
I MEAN, IT JUST SUCKS.

22:57.375 --> 22:58.959
CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?

22:59.875 --> 23:02.166
MAYBE I'M
MISINTERPRETING THINGS,

23:02.166 --> 23:05.000
BUT I REALLY THOUGHT YOU
WANTED TO SLEEP WITH ME.

23:06.083 --> 23:07.333
SOMETHING SEEMED
TO CHANGE YOUR MIND

23:07.333 --> 23:09.417
THAT NIGHT
ON THE BEACH.

23:10.375 --> 23:12.875
IT JUST WASN'T
THE RIGHT TIME.

23:18.208 --> 23:21.375
IS THERE EVER GONNA
BE A RIGHT TIME?

23:21.375 --> 23:25.125
DAWSON, IF I GO TO BOSTON
AND YOU GO TO L.A...

23:25.125 --> 23:27.750
GETTING CLOSER IS JUST GONNA
MAKE THINGS MORE PAINFUL.

23:27.750 --> 23:29.708
WHAT MADE YOU
DECIDE TO APPLY

23:29.708 --> 23:30.750
FOR A JOB
IN BOSTON?

23:30.750 --> 23:32.875
YOU'RE LEAVING...

23:32.875 --> 23:36.083
AND I AM SO UNBELIEVABLY
HAPPY FOR YOU, BUT--

23:36.083 --> 23:38.041
LOOK, I CAN'T TAKE
THAT NEXT STEP,

23:38.041 --> 23:39.291
OPEN MYSELF UP LIKE THAT
JUST TO BE LEFT.

23:39.291 --> 23:41.750
I JUST CAN'T DO THAT.

23:41.750 --> 23:43.125
YOU KNOW,
I'VE GOTTA GET ON
WITH MY OWN LIFE.

23:43.125 --> 23:45.250
[DOOR OPENS]

23:45.250 --> 23:47.083
IT'S NOT HAPPENING.

23:47.083 --> 23:48.875
NOT TODAY.

23:48.875 --> 23:50.500
FALSE ALARM.

23:50.500 --> 23:50.750
OH...

23:53.458 --> 23:56.166
Mitch: HERE, HONEY.
THIS SHOULD HELP A BIT.

23:57.750 --> 23:59.667
[SIGHS]

24:04.208 --> 24:05.959
[CAR DOOR SLAMS]

24:13.583 --> 24:16.917
HEY, I'M JUST AS
SURPRISED AS YOU ARE.

24:16.917 --> 24:18.000
I JUST--

24:18.000 --> 24:20.792
I DIDN'T REALLY HAVE
ANYWHERE ELSE TO GO.

24:20.792 --> 24:22.667
WELL, COME IN.

24:27.625 --> 24:29.875
PLAN ON LEAVING
THE COUNTRY?

24:29.875 --> 24:30.667
UH, NO.

24:30.667 --> 24:32.625
ACTUALLY, I HAVE
AN INTERVIEW

24:32.625 --> 24:34.959
FOR A MAGAZINE JOB
IN BOSTON.

24:38.834 --> 24:40.375
HOW ARE YOU
HOLDING UP?

24:43.667 --> 24:45.291
WELL...

24:45.291 --> 24:46.458
CONSIDERING I'VE TURNED
INTO THIS CRAZY PERSON

24:46.458 --> 24:48.792
THAT I DON'T
EVEN RECOGNIZE...

24:49.208 --> 24:51.041
GREAT.

24:52.959 --> 24:55.959
GOD, I...

24:55.959 --> 24:58.583
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HOW ILL-PREPARED
I AM FOR THIS.

24:59.208 --> 25:02.000
WHAT WAS I THINKING?

25:02.000 --> 25:03.834
YOU FELL IN LOVE,
YOU HAD SEX.

25:03.834 --> 25:05.875
I MEAN, EVEN IF YOU
TAKE EVERY PRECAUTION,

25:05.875 --> 25:08.917
IT'S BOUND TO CHANGE
YOUR WORLD COMPLETELY.

25:08.917 --> 25:09.834
[LAUGHS]

25:09.834 --> 25:12.834
COULD YOU IMAGINE
PACEY WITH A BABY?

25:12.834 --> 25:14.250
[LAUGHS]

25:14.250 --> 25:16.333
YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY,
'CAUSE I THINK PACEY

25:16.333 --> 25:18.166
WOULD PROBABLY LIKE
THE IDEA OF A BABY.

25:18.166 --> 25:20.000
I MEAN, HE'S
GREAT WITH KIDS,

25:20.000 --> 25:20.834
ATTENTIVE TO WOMEN.

25:20.834 --> 25:22.500
THE PROBLEM
WITH THE SCENARIO

25:22.500 --> 25:24.375
IS THAT PACEY JUST
CAN'T DEAL WITH PACEY.

25:24.375 --> 25:25.917
I KNOW,
AND BELIEVE ME,

25:25.917 --> 25:27.041
THE LAST THING
I WANT TO DO

25:27.041 --> 25:29.792
IS MAKE HIS LIFE
MORE DIFFICULT, BUT...

25:29.792 --> 25:31.750
[SIGHS]

25:31.750 --> 25:33.625
I REALLY NEED HIM
RIGHT NOW, GRETCHEN.

25:35.166 --> 25:35.625
HAVE YOU TOLD BESSIE?

25:38.750 --> 25:40.792
PRETTY MUCH.

25:40.792 --> 25:41.542
RIGHT AFTER
I TOLD HER

25:41.542 --> 25:43.750
THAT HER LIFE
DISGUSTS ME.

25:46.417 --> 25:48.417
LOOK, MAKE AMENDS
WITH YOUR SISTER, JOEY.

25:48.417 --> 25:50.750
I MEAN,
BEING PREGNANT,

25:50.750 --> 25:51.708
WHETHER YOU CHOOSE
TO STAY THAT WAY OR NOT,

25:51.708 --> 25:53.417
IS ULTIMATELY
ABOUT FAMILY.

25:53.417 --> 25:54.375
AND TRUST ME,

25:54.375 --> 25:55.834
YOU'RE GONNA WANT
THAT SUPPORT SYSTEM

25:55.834 --> 25:57.083
AROUND YOU.

25:58.208 --> 25:59.875
YOU SOUND LIKE YOU'RE
PRETTY FAMILIAR

25:59.875 --> 26:01.417
WITH THIS SITUATION.

26:04.708 --> 26:08.083
LAST YEAR, IN COLLEGE...

26:08.083 --> 26:08.708
I MISCARRIED.

26:12.458 --> 26:13.625
I'M SORRY.

26:17.208 --> 26:18.667
[SIGHS]

26:21.250 --> 26:23.041
THAT'S WHY
I CAME BACK HERE.

26:23.041 --> 26:24.875
TO DEAL
WITH EVERYTHING.

26:24.875 --> 26:27.542
EVERYTHING THAT YOU'RE
DEALING WITH NOW.

26:31.917 --> 26:34.250
WELL, YOU'VE
BEEN SUCCESSFUL.

26:34.250 --> 26:35.458
I MEAN...

26:35.458 --> 26:38.708
NEW BOYFRIEND,
MAYBE A NEW JOB.

26:39.750 --> 26:43.542
IS DAWSON GONNA GO
TO BOSTON WITH YOU?

26:43.542 --> 26:46.417
NO, DAWSON AND I ARE IN
VERY DIFFERENT PLACES

26:46.417 --> 26:48.291
IN OUR LIVES.

26:50.542 --> 26:54.583
GRETCHEN, YOU DO KNOW
THAT DAWSON WOULD LASSO
THE MOON FOR YOU, RIGHT?

26:58.291 --> 26:59.708
I KNOW...

26:59.708 --> 27:03.083
BUT HOW CAN I LET
SOMEONE DO THAT

27:03.083 --> 27:05.333
WHEN HE'S
ABOUT TO LEAVE?

27:05.333 --> 27:08.250
YOU DON'T SHUT HIM
OUT OF YOUR LIFE.

27:09.708 --> 27:11.667
AND YOU CHERISH
THAT BIG PART OF HIM

27:11.667 --> 27:13.750
THAT HE ALWAYS
WANTS YOU TO HAVE.

27:14.542 --> 27:17.708
NO MATTER
WHAT HAPPENS...

27:19.125 --> 27:22.458
YOU NEVER FORGET HIM.

27:27.792 --> 27:30.291
Mitch: WHO WANTS TO WATCH
ANDREW DICE CLAY?

27:30.291 --> 27:31.708
I DELETED A BUNCH
OF SAPPY DATE MOVIES.

27:31.708 --> 27:33.625
NOW IT THINKS I'M
A MISOGYNISTIC CYNIC.

27:33.625 --> 27:35.125
OH, MITCH, THE CONTRACTIONS
ARE GETTING STRONGER.

27:35.125 --> 27:36.750
THIS IS IT.
IT'S DEFINITELY TIME.

27:36.750 --> 27:37.500
HONEY, DON'T YOU
THINK YOU OUGHT
TO WAIT A WHILE?

27:37.500 --> 27:38.500
JUST TILL
YOU'RE POSITIVE.

27:38.500 --> 27:40.834
OH, I AM
QUITE POSITIVE.

27:40.834 --> 27:41.959
AAH!

27:41.959 --> 27:42.542
HOW ABOUT
RESERVOIR DOGS?

27:42.542 --> 27:44.208
I SAID IT'S TIME.

27:44.208 --> 27:45.792
HEY...

27:45.792 --> 27:47.125
I AM GOING
TO HAVE A BABY.

27:47.125 --> 27:48.500
NOW, GET OFF
THE SOFA

27:48.500 --> 27:50.166
AND GET YOUR ASS
IN THE CAR!

27:50.166 --> 27:51.041
THAT HURTS.

27:51.041 --> 27:53.708
DON'T TALK TO ME
ABOUT PAIN. DON'T.

27:53.708 --> 27:55.750
I THINK SHE MEANS IT
THIS TIME.

27:55.750 --> 27:57.375
[KNOCKING]

28:00.500 --> 28:02.000
WAS IT THE "GO"
OR THE "AWAY"

28:02.000 --> 28:03.375
THAT TRIPPED YOU UP?

28:03.375 --> 28:04.417
THIS IS OFFICER SULLIVAN.

28:04.417 --> 28:06.667
HE'S THE YOUTH OFFICER
AT CAPESIDE.

28:07.625 --> 28:08.500
NICE TO MEET YOU.

28:08.500 --> 28:10.291
OH, BOY, I KNEW
I SHOULDN'T HAVE

28:10.291 --> 28:12.750
RIPPED THAT TAG
OFF MY MATTRESS.

28:12.750 --> 28:15.333
HE'S GONNA MAKE SURE
THAT THE RIGHT PEOPLE
PAY ATTENTION TO THIS.

28:15.333 --> 28:17.208
YEAH, SURE.

28:19.667 --> 28:20.708
LOOK, I KNOW
YOU'RE SCARED.

28:20.708 --> 28:22.333
YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

28:22.333 --> 28:23.166
YOU HAVE TO REPORT THIS.

28:23.166 --> 28:24.917
HOW DARE YOU COME
INTO MY HOUSE

28:24.917 --> 28:26.000
AND TELL ME WHAT
I HAVE TO DO.

28:26.000 --> 28:27.500
YOU'RE LUCKY MY PARENTS
AREN'T HERE RIGHT NOW.

28:27.500 --> 28:30.333
ARE THEY THE ONES
TELLING YOU NOT
TO TALK ABOUT THIS?

28:30.333 --> 28:31.417
BECAUSE FOR
THE LIFE OF ME,

28:31.417 --> 28:32.875
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY THEY DIDN'T MAKE YOU

28:32.875 --> 28:34.583
CALL THE COPS
2 DAYS AGO.

28:34.583 --> 28:36.458
BECAUSE MAYBE,
LIKE ME,

28:36.458 --> 28:37.041
ALL THEY WANT
TO DO IS FORGET

28:37.041 --> 28:37.959
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

28:37.959 --> 28:38.875
WHICH GROWS
INCREASINGLY DIFFICULT

28:38.875 --> 28:41.208
EVERY TIME YOU SHOW
YOUR FACE HERE.

28:41.208 --> 28:42.959
NOW PLEASE, JUST GO.

28:42.959 --> 28:44.208
Sullivan: THE ODDS
WEREN'T IN YOUR FAVOR

28:44.208 --> 28:45.875
THE OTHER NIGHT, TOBEY.
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?

28:45.875 --> 28:46.000
EXCUSE ME?

28:47.959 --> 28:50.166
TOBEY, YOU'RE
3 TIMES MORE LIKELY

28:50.166 --> 28:51.667
TO BE THREATENED
BY SOMEONE

28:51.667 --> 28:53.375
WITH A WEAPON
THAN A STRAIGHT KID.

28:53.375 --> 28:56.125
THERE'S A 70% CHANCE
OF YOU BEING HARASSED,

28:56.125 --> 28:59.417
AND A 30% CHANCE
THAT SOMEONE'S GONNA...

28:59.417 --> 29:01.000
DO THIS TO YOU.

29:01.000 --> 29:03.917
WHICH IS WHY I NEED
FOR YOU TO TALK TO ME
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

29:05.875 --> 29:08.000
MOST KIDS, THEY DON'T
HAVE THE STRENGTH.

29:08.834 --> 29:11.250
OR THEY DON'T
GET THE CHANCE.

29:11.250 --> 29:12.875
OR HAVE THE FRIENDS
TO SUPPORT THEM.

29:24.250 --> 29:25.834
[SIGHS]

29:27.083 --> 29:28.458
I WAS, UH...

29:28.458 --> 29:29.834
WAITING FOR THE BUS
ON MARKET AND 16th

29:29.834 --> 29:33.000
WHEN THIS GUY
CAME UP NEXT TO ME.

29:33.000 --> 29:35.542
HE WAS TALL, UH,

29:35.542 --> 29:37.041
BLACK HAIR.

29:37.041 --> 29:38.917
I'D SEEN HIM
A COUPLE NIGHTS BEFORE.

29:38.917 --> 29:41.750
I--I MADE SOME STUPID
SMALL TALK OR SOMETHING

29:41.750 --> 29:44.875
ABOUT THE BUSSES
RUNNING LATE.

29:44.875 --> 29:48.542
AND THEN I LOOKED HIM
IN THE EYES...

29:48.542 --> 29:51.250
AND SMILED AT HIM.

29:51.250 --> 29:52.792
I GUESS I SHOULDN'T HAVE
DONE THAT OR SOMETHING,

29:52.792 --> 29:55.708
BECAUSE HE YELLED
"FAGGOT" AT ME

29:55.708 --> 29:57.959
OR SOMETHING,
AND THEN...

29:57.959 --> 29:59.917
BEFORE I KNEW IT,
THERE WAS SOMEBODY ELSE.

30:02.625 --> 30:04.291
UH, A FRIEND
OF HIS OR SOMETHING

30:04.291 --> 30:05.959
CAME OUT OF NOWHERE.

30:05.959 --> 30:08.291
AND ONE HELD ME
WHILE THE OTHER ONE

30:08.291 --> 30:09.750
JUST STARTED
WAILING ON ME.

30:09.750 --> 30:11.792
PUNCHING ME
IN THE FACE,

30:11.792 --> 30:12.875
KICKING ME...

30:12.875 --> 30:15.083
AND THEN
AT SOME POINT

30:15.083 --> 30:15.792
I JUST FELL
TO THE GROUND.

30:15.792 --> 30:18.208
THIS ISN'T YOUR FAULT.

30:20.458 --> 30:23.291
ALL I DID WAS
SMILE AT HIM.

30:41.041 --> 30:42.125
I NOW KNOW
WAY TOO MUCH

30:42.125 --> 30:44.875
ABOUT THE HOSPITAL
PARKING ATTENDANT'S LIFE.

30:46.166 --> 30:47.917
YOUR MOTHER'S BEEN
IN HARD LABOR ALL NIGHT.

30:47.917 --> 30:49.750
HOW'S SHE DOING?

30:49.750 --> 30:51.500
I DON'T KNOW.

30:51.500 --> 30:53.166
QUITE FRANKLY,
THAT WORRIES ME.

30:53.166 --> 30:56.458
THERE'S A LOT OF WHISPERING
GOING ON OVER THERE.

30:57.792 --> 30:59.875
TELL THEM
YOU WANT TO KNOW.

30:59.875 --> 31:01.917
BEEN THERE.
ALL I GET IS

31:01.917 --> 31:02.875
"RELAX, MR. LEERY.

31:02.875 --> 31:06.834
HELP YOUR WIFE FOCUS
ON HER BREATHING."

31:06.834 --> 31:08.417
Gale: AAH! MITCH!

31:08.417 --> 31:10.834
[SIGHS]

31:13.875 --> 31:16.375
I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

31:30.166 --> 31:31.708
WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP?

31:31.708 --> 31:33.500
I GET UP AT DAWN
EVERY MORNING.

31:33.500 --> 31:35.959
IT'S THE ONLY TIME
I HAVE TO MYSELF.

31:38.959 --> 31:41.041
I SPENT THE NIGHT
AT GRETCHEN'S.

31:43.375 --> 31:45.375
DO YOU KNOW I ONCE
CLIMBED INTO YOUR CRIB

31:45.375 --> 31:46.417
AND PUSHED YOU OUT?

31:47.834 --> 31:49.041
DID YOU DROP ME
ON MY HEAD?

31:49.041 --> 31:51.125
BECAUSE THAT WOULD
EXPLAIN A LOT.

31:52.708 --> 31:55.417
BEFORE YOU CAME ALONG,

31:55.417 --> 31:57.000
MOM AND I HAD
A GOOD THING GOING.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.834
I HATED YOU.

31:59.834 --> 32:02.125
YOU HATED ME
'CAUSE YOU WERE JEALOUS.

32:02.125 --> 32:03.750
YOU HATED ME
BECAUSE I WAS

32:03.750 --> 32:05.542
TAKING YOUR MOM
AWAY, BUT...

32:07.291 --> 32:09.041
MOSTLY YOU HATED ME
BECAUSE YOU KNEW

32:09.041 --> 32:10.125
YOU'D ALWAYS HAVE
TO TAKE CARE OF ME.

32:12.375 --> 32:15.667
I REALLY DID WANT
YOUR LIFE TO BE
BETTER THAN MINE.

32:15.667 --> 32:18.417
BESSIE,
YOU WENT FIRST.

32:18.417 --> 32:21.750
YOU TOOK ON THE FULL
BRUNT OF THIS STORM.

32:21.750 --> 32:23.792
AND YOU DIDN'T DO
WHAT OTHERS WOULD HAVE.

32:23.792 --> 32:26.000
YOU DIDN'T RUN,
YOU DIDN'T COWER,

32:26.000 --> 32:26.917
YOU CREATED THIS

32:26.917 --> 32:30.417
WARM, LOVING,
SAFE PLACE.

32:32.417 --> 32:33.792
AND YOU RAISED A BABY

32:33.792 --> 32:37.083
AND A LITTLE SISTER.

32:38.375 --> 32:42.291
I HOPE I WOULD
HAVE THE STRENGTH
AND COURAGE TO...

32:42.291 --> 32:43.291
CREATE A LIFE
FOR MYSELF

32:43.291 --> 32:45.875
THAT'S EVEN
REMOTELY LIKE YOURS.

32:57.041 --> 32:59.500
I JUST WANT YOU
TO KNOW I LOVE YOU

32:59.500 --> 33:01.125
AND I'M HERE FOR YOU
IF--IF YOU WANT ME.

33:07.458 --> 33:08.291
[ALEXANDER CRIES]

33:10.625 --> 33:13.166
ANOTHER DAY.

33:28.500 --> 33:30.750
[KNOCKING]

33:31.417 --> 33:33.041
OH, WHAT NOW?
OPRAH?

33:33.041 --> 33:34.667
YOU DIDN'T THINK
I WAS GOING

33:34.667 --> 33:35.667
TO TUTORING
WITHOUT YOU?

33:35.667 --> 33:36.667
UH, IF YOU
HAVEN'T NOTICED,

33:36.667 --> 33:38.000
I'M NOT EXACTLY
PRESENTABLE.

33:38.000 --> 33:40.208
WELL, THEN, WE'LL
TELL 'EM YOU FELL
OFF YOUR SKATEBOARD.

33:40.208 --> 33:41.500
THEY'RE KIDS, JACK.
NOT IMBECILES.

33:41.500 --> 33:45.125
FINE. THEN WE'LL
TELL 'EM YOU FELL
OFF YOUR HIGH HORSE.

33:45.125 --> 33:47.333
WHATEVER. YOU'RE
NOT GONNA SIT AROUND
THE HOUSE ALL DAY.

33:47.333 --> 33:47.834
GET YOUR COAT.

33:47.834 --> 33:49.667
WHAT IS THIS?

33:49.667 --> 33:51.500
A COUPLE OF MONTHS AGO,
YOU WERE ALL ABOUT

33:51.500 --> 33:52.792
NOT GETTING INVOLVED,

33:52.792 --> 33:55.500
AND SUDDENLY YOU'RE
SOME BIG HOMO ACTIVIST?

33:55.500 --> 33:57.250
MAYBE I'M JUST
A TOBEY ACTIVIST.

33:57.250 --> 33:58.333
[LAUGHS]

33:58.333 --> 34:00.166
OH, AS MUCH AS MY EGO
WOULD LIKE TO BUY

34:00.166 --> 34:02.000
THAT ATTRACTIVE PIECE
OF MERCHANDISE,

34:02.000 --> 34:03.291
SOMEHOW IT DOESN'T
QUITE FIT.

34:04.500 --> 34:06.291
WHAT'S HAPPENED
TO YOU, JACK?

34:06.291 --> 34:09.375
IT'S MORE LIKE
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

34:09.375 --> 34:11.000
SOMEDAY, I'M GONNA WANT
TO WALK THROUGH THE PARK

34:11.000 --> 34:12.542
AND I'M GONNA WANT
TO HOLD SOME GUY'S HAND

34:12.542 --> 34:13.875
AND...

34:13.875 --> 34:15.041
WHAT IF I FORGET
TO LOOK AROUND FIRST?

34:15.041 --> 34:17.417
WHAT IF THE WRONG
PEOPLE SEE ME DO THAT?

34:17.417 --> 34:18.250
WE'RE NOT SO DIFFERENT,
YOU AND I.

34:18.250 --> 34:19.917
I USED TO THINK
THAT WE WERE,

34:19.917 --> 34:20.958
BUT WE'RE NOT.

34:22.291 --> 34:25.125
IF I WOULD HAVE LEFT EARLY,
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN ME.

34:25.125 --> 34:27.250
AND YOU'RE JUST NOW
REALIZING THIS?

34:28.875 --> 34:30.375
YEAH. BETTER LATE
THAN NEVER.

34:30.375 --> 34:31.625
YEAH, AND BETTER
ON TIME THAN LATE.

34:31.625 --> 34:33.542
[LAUGHS]

34:33.542 --> 34:34.708
COME ON, MAN. IT'S
WAY TOO EARLY IN THE DAY

34:34.708 --> 34:35.875
FOR ONE OF
YOUR LECTURES.

34:35.875 --> 34:37.041
OY!

34:37.041 --> 34:38.375
YOU KNOW, IF YOU WERE
REALLY A TOBEY ACTIVIST,

34:38.375 --> 34:40.583
YOU WOULD HAVE CARRIED
ME DOWN THE STEPS.

34:40.583 --> 34:43.667
YEAH, DON'T PUSH
YOUR LUCK, MAN.

35:00.125 --> 35:02.083
[SIGHS]

35:04.458 --> 35:06.583
[SIGHS]

35:18.750 --> 35:21.208
HOW IS SHE?

35:21.208 --> 35:22.208
UH...

35:22.208 --> 35:23.083
[SIGHS]

35:23.083 --> 35:24.542
SHE'S BEEN
IN THERE ALL NIGHT

35:24.542 --> 35:25.750
AND ALL DAY
AND I'M--

35:25.750 --> 35:27.125
I'M STARTING
TO GET THE IMPRESSION

35:27.125 --> 35:28.875
THINGS AREN'T
PROGRESSING THE WAY
THEY'RE SUPPOSED TO.

35:28.875 --> 35:30.125
IT CAN BE A LONG
PROCESS, DAWSON.

35:30.125 --> 35:32.792
YEAH, I'M SURE
SHE'LL BE FINE.

35:32.792 --> 35:35.834
HEY, UM, IS...

35:40.250 --> 35:41.333
[SIGHS]

35:41.333 --> 35:41.417
EXCUSE ME.

35:45.625 --> 35:47.417
DAWSON.

35:56.083 --> 35:57.291
[LAUGHS]

35:57.291 --> 35:58.208
A COUPLE OF
WEEKS AGO,

35:58.208 --> 35:59.792
I'M WANDERING
THROUGH THESE HALLS,

35:59.792 --> 36:01.291
PRAYING FOR SOMEBODY
TO DIE.

36:01.291 --> 36:02.500
AND NOW HERE I AM,
SAME HALLS,

36:02.500 --> 36:04.500
PRAYING FOR SOMEBODY
TO BE BORN.

36:05.375 --> 36:06.375
IS IT JUST ME,
OR DID LIFE

36:06.375 --> 36:07.708
SUDDENLY BROADEN
THIS YEAR?

36:08.291 --> 36:10.667
IT'S NOT JUST YOU.

36:10.667 --> 36:12.708
I...

36:12.708 --> 36:15.166
THINK THE STAKES
HAVE BEEN RAISED

36:15.166 --> 36:16.166
FOR EVERYONE.

36:16.166 --> 36:18.083
HAVE YOU AND PACEY
TALKED ABOUT HIM

36:18.083 --> 36:18.291
BEING NEAR WORTHINGTON
NEXT YEAR?

36:20.083 --> 36:21.834
[LAUGHS]

36:21.834 --> 36:23.291
UH, PACEY AND I
HAVEN'T REALLY DISCUSSED

36:23.291 --> 36:23.834
THE FUTURE
TOO MUCH LATELY.

36:23.834 --> 36:26.333
YOU SHOULD.

36:26.333 --> 36:28.166
IT HAS A PECULIAR WAY
OF UNEXPECTEDLY

36:28.166 --> 36:30.041
BECOMING THE PRESENT.

36:33.417 --> 36:36.041
DAWSON, GRETCHEN
IS CRAZY ABOUT YOU.

36:36.041 --> 36:37.708
SHE TOLD ME LAST NIGHT.

36:37.708 --> 36:40.959
THEN YOU PROBABLY
ALSO KNOW THAT SHE'S
ON A TRAIN RIGHT NOW

36:40.959 --> 36:42.583
FOR BOSTON WHERE SHE'S
PROBABLY GONNA BE LIVING.

36:42.583 --> 36:44.000
